knowledge_graph.title: Solar car
knowledge_graph.description: A solar car is a solar vehicle used for land transport. related_questions.question: How does a solar car work?
related_questions.snippet: True solar-powered cars are actually electric vehicles that are powered by solar panels . The panels are used produce electricity by converting the sun's rays into energy, which is then stored in solar batteries. The car runs by using the energy that is stored in the batteries.
related_questions.title: How Do Solar Cars Work? - Solar Power

related_questions.question: How do you make a car run on solar power?
related_questions.snippet: That electricity then fuels the battery that runs the car's motor. Instead of using a battery, some solar cars direct the power straight to an electric motor. Solar cars can accomplish this through photovoltaic cells (PVC). PVCs are the components in solar paneling that convert the sun's energy to electricity.
